==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ramify
<hw>Ram"i*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To shoot, or
divide, into branches or subdivisions, as the stem of a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When they [asparagus plants] . . . begin to <qex>ramify</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be divided or subdivided, as a main
subject.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ramigerous</ent>⟦br⟧
